  <title>Gio.TlsClientConnection.prototype.set_use_ssl3</title>
  <synopsis><code mime="text/x-gjs">
function set_use_ssl3(use_ssl3: Boolean): void {
    // Gjs wrapper for g_tls_client_connection_set_use_ssl3()
}
  </code></synopsis>
  <p>If <code>use_ssl3</code> is <code>true</code>, this forces <code>conn</code> to use SSL 3.0 rather than
trying to properly negotiate the right version of TLS or SSL to use.
This can be used when talking to servers that do not implement the
fallbacks correctly and which will therefore fail to handshake with
a "modern" TLS handshake attempt.</p>
  <p>Since 2.28</p>
